\title{Comaximal ideals}
\author{alex-nelson}
\import{notation}
\date{2025-12-18}
\taxon{definition}
\meta{source}{Dummit and Foote [[dummit-2004-abstract]] Section 7.6}

\p{Let #{R} be a unital [[ra-0003]]. Let #{A\ideal R} and #{B\ideal R} be [ideals](ra-0011) of #{R}. We say #{A} and #{B} are \define{Comaximal} if their [sum](ra-0025) is the entire ring #{A+B=R}.}

\p{We see that this is a symmetric predicate in #{A} and #{B} since #{A+B=B+A}.}